Simply put, the section uses a variety of research tools to estimate the benefit that healthcare is delivering so we can get more “bang” from our healthcare “buck,” a particularly important concern for the United States, which spends far more money on healthcare per-capita than any other country, yet delivers benefits that are often modest and unevenly distributed. Simply put, the section uses a variety of research tools to estimate the benefit that healthcare is delivering so we can get more “bang” from our healthcare “buck,” a particularly important concern for the United States, which spends far more money on healthcare per-capita than any other country, yet delivers benefits that are often modest and unevenly distributed.
